      "body" : "Thanks @MarcoFalke. I'm not a fan of leaving unexecuted lines in the test code just in case the product code is changed in the future. Re-adding a few asserts in this test case is negligible effort compared to actually adding the functionality to bitcoin core (which would require significant changes to the mining code). \r\n\r\nAnd if writing 7 assert lines is really too much effort, git history is a far better place to keep this dead code :)",
